parameters:
Hmm, well done. However, I find it hard to believe all of a
sudden... Minister, is what this person saying true?

The information regarding the conflict zone and invasion
procedure... it aligns with the facts in the document.
Furthermore, it bears the signature of King Cordin... the
handwriting is likely...

To determine if it is the real thing... I have been concerned
since power was transferred to that troublemaker... It's becoming
a reality...

Well done, Vega. I shall welcome you all under the protection of
Ulyssean.

I hear that you were born into one of the prominent noble
families in Cordin. Why did you choose not to live in his
country, without choosing the path of betraying your homeland?

\SE[20]My Lira family is of proud lineage. \!\SE[19]...Though we
have fallen, we have not stooped so low as to enjoy the happiness
that is built upon the sacrifice of innocent people.

\SE[67]... As someone in the lowest position. \. I have chosen
the path that I believe is right.

\SE[53]Is that really all? Vega, is it? \SE[50]Can you really
abandon your country just based on a sense of duty? Is that all
there is to your true feelings?

\SE[18]The reason my Lira family.... \!\SE[19]My father's death
was caused by Cordin, that's why.

\SE[20]My father was both a businessman and an investor.
\!\SE[75]His final project was an investment in mining
development.... The soil was prepared and there were prospects
for production.... \!\SE[66]But Cordin took it all away.

\SE[66]Earlier, I mentioned that I was driven by a sense of
justice... But more than that, I am driven by personal grudges.
\SE[19]... That is my everything now.

\SE[53]Are you... fighting solely to avenge your father's regret?
\SE[50]Is that the only reason you're fighting?
\SE[50]... Even if you perceive it that way, it doesn't matter.

\SE[16]Ahaha...! How interesting. \SE[51]I understand! I respect
your determination. \SE[52]I will fully support you, Ulysseene!

\SE[68]Oh, this is more than I deserve... \!\SE[67]I don't even
have words to thank you.

H-Hey, don't decide things on your own. There's a proper
procedure for this...

\SE[54]What are you saying, Father! Taking on the feelings of the
deceased! It's admirable, isn't it! \!\SE[35]Besides, this is how
it was bound to turn out, right!?

\SE[54]It seems like the neighboring country is about to attack
us any moment now! \SE[50]We have no choice but to defend
ourselves!

That's true, but things like appearances are important. First,
you should start with that...

\SE[2] (I thought it was a cute country.... \!\SE[15]Even the
kings are cute people.)
